gnd check — validate every ID citation across the repo (the default subcommand).

Usage:  gnd [check] [PATH] [--require-grounding] [--format text|json]

PATH defaults to `.`; config (`.agents/gnd.toml`) is discovered by walking up from it.
With no config, gnd scans `docs/`, `e2e/`, and `src/`; set `[scan] include` to widen it.
Pointing gnd at an explicit PATH scans exactly that file or directory.
`gnd PATH` is shorthand for `gnd check PATH` — byte-for-byte equivalent.

Options:
  --format text|json   text (default) prints `success` or `path:line: message`; json emits NDJSON.
  --require-grounding  also require every source file to cite a declared ID ([reference] require_grounding).

Findings go to stdout (the linter convention) — `gnd check | …` and `gnd check
--format json | jq` need no redirect. Only run-level `error:` / `warning:` lines
(unreadable path, empty scan) go to stderr; a clean text run prints `success`.

Exit:  0 clean · 1 dangling / duplicate / unknown-section / ungrounded findings · 2 unreadable tree or CLI error.

Examples:
  gnd                    # check the whole repo
  gnd docs/              # check one subtree
  gnd --format json | jq # machine-readable diagnostics for CI
